<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">
Species complex. Originally described from the Gulf of Naples. 
<bibRefCitation author="Maltagliati, F." journalOrPublisher="Marine Biology" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="871 - 879" title="Is Syllisgracilis (Polychaeta: Syllidae) a species complex? An allozyme perspective" volume="136" year="2000">Maltagliati et al. (2000)</bibRefCitation>
found two cryptic species of 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Syllis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Syllis gracilis" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="gracilis">Syllis gracilis</taxonomicName>
in Sardinia and western Italy, 
<bibRefCitation author="Alvarez-Campos, Patricia" journalOrPublisher="Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="138 - 150" title="The Syllisgracilis species complex: a molecular approach to a difficult taxonomic problem (Annelida, Syllidae)" volume="109" year="2016">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Álvarez-Campos">Alvarez-Campos</normalizedToken>
et al. (2016)
</bibRefCitation>
recover three cryptic species in the Mediterranean: one from Sicily and two from the North-Western Mediterranean. No material from the Eastern Mediterranean was studied, and specimens from Greece could belong to any of these or a different species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
